I"F<h2 id="-1-optimal-interpolation-"><span style="color:blue"> 1. Optimal interpolation </span></h2>

<p>Resulting correction <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/gif.latex?x_i%5E%7Ba%7D" alt="equation" /> can be expressed as a weighted linear combination 
of the differences between observed and modeled time series 
<img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%5CDelta_n%28%5Ctau%29%20%3D%20y_n%5E%7Bo%7D%28%5Ctau%29-Hx_n%5E%7Bb%7D%28%5Ctau%29" alt="equation" /></p>

<p><img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%5CDelta_n%28%5Ctau%29%20%3D%20y_n%5E%7Bo%7D%28%5Ctau%29-Hx_n%5E%7Bb%7D%28%5Ctau%29" alt="equation" /></p>

<p>\[x_i^{a}(t) = x_i^{b}(t) + \sum_{n=1}^{N} \sum_{\tau=t-T}^{t+T} w_n^{(i,t)}(\tau)\Delta_n(\tau)\]</p>

<p><img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?x_i%5E%7Ba%7D%28t%29%20%3D%20x_i%5E%7Bb%7D%28t%29%20&plus;%20%5Csum_%7Bn%3D1%7D%5E%7BN%7D%20%5Csum_%7B%5Ctau%3Dt-T%7D%5E%7Bt&plus;T%7D%20w_n%5E%7B%28i%2Ct%29%7D%28%5Ctau%29%5CDelta_n%28%5Ctau%29" alt="equation" /></p>

<p>where:</p>

<p><img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?N" alt="equation" /> - number of observation points,</p>

<p><img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?t" alt="equation" /> - time instance of the background model, \n
<img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?T" alt="equation" /> - maximum time lag that depends on the variability of the studied process.</p>

<p>The conventional OI results in the Best Linear Unbiased Estimate (BLUE) <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%5Ctextbf%7Bx%7D%5E%7Ba%7D" alt="equation" /> of the true system state column vector 
<img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%5Ctextbf%7Bx%7D%5E%7Bt%7D" alt="equation" /> having available vector of observations <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%5Ctextbf%7By%7D%5E%7Bo%7D" alt="equation" />, 
initial background field state vector <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%5Ctextbf%7Bx%7D%5E%7Bb%7D" alt="equation" />, and estimated error covariances:</p>

<p><img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%5Ctextbf%7Bx%7D%5E%7Ba%7D%3D%5Ctextbf%7Bx%7D%5E%7Bb%7D&plus;%5Ctextbf%7BK%7D%28%5Ctextbf%7By%7D%5E%7Bo%7D-%5Ctextbf%7BH%7D%5Ctextbf%7Bx%7D%5E%7Bb%7D%29" alt="equation" /></p>

<p><img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%5Ctextbf%7BK%7D%3D%5Ctextbf%7BP%7D%5E%7Bb%7D%5Ctextbf%7BH%7D%5E%7BT%7D%28%5Ctextbf%7BH%7D%5Ctextbf%7BP%7D%5Eb%5Ctextbf%7BH%7D%5E%7BT%7D&plus;%5Ctextbf%7BR%7D%29%5E%7B-1%7D" alt="equation" /></p>

<p>where:<br />
<img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%5Ctextbf%7BP%7D%5Eb%20%3D%20%5Clangle%20%28%5Ctextbf%7Bx%7D%5Eb%20-%20%5Ctextbf%7Bx%7D%5Et%29%7B%28%5Ctextbf%7Bx%7D%5Eb%20-%20%5Ctextbf%7Bx%7D%5Et%29%7D%5ET%20%5Crangle%24%20and%20%24%5Ctextbf%7BR%7D%20%3D%20%5Clangle%20%28%5Ctextbf%7By%7D%5Eo%20-%20%5Ctextbf%7Bx%7D%5Et%29%7B%28%5Ctextbf%7By%7D%5Eo%20-%20%5Ctextbf%7Bx%7D%5Et%29%7D%5ET%20%5Crangle" alt="equation" /> are the matrices of estimated covariances of the background field and observation errors, respectively;<br />
<img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%5Ctextbf%7BH%7D" alt="equation" /> - the representation matrix of mapping observations onto the corresponding model grid;<br />
<img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%5Cmathbf%7BK%7D" alt="equation" /> - the weight matrix referred to as the Kalman gains, since the OI corresponds to the analysis stage of the Kalman filter.</p>
